      <title>#240 - The Boundaries of Self</title>
      <pubDate>Sun, 07 Mar 2021 23:38:44 -0500</pubDate>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">1572151</guid>
      <link>https://samharris.org/subscriber-extras/240-boundaries-self/</link>
      <itunes:subtitle>A Conversation with David Whyte</itunes:subtitle>
      <description><![CDATA[<span style="font-weight: 400;">In this episode of the podcast, Sam speaks with poet David Whyte about his new and on-going series for the Waking Up app, based on his book, </span><a href="https://amzn.to/3t0pn6W" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Consolations: The Solace, Nourishment and Underlying Meaning of Everyday Words</span></i></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">With the imagery of a poet and the reflection of a philosopher, David turns his attention to ordinary words, each a doorway into the underlying currents of human life.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">They discuss 4 tracks from the first installment—</span><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Friendship</span></i><span style="font-weight: 400;">, </span><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Honesty</span></i><span style="font-weight: 400;">, </span><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Ambition,</span></i><span style="font-weight: 400;"> and </span><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Alone.</span></i>

<b>David Whyte</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> is a poet and the author of 10 books of poetry along with four books of prose. David holds a degree in Marine Zoology, honorary degrees from Neumann College and Royal Roads University, and has traveled extensively, including living and working as a naturalist guide in the Galapagos Islands and leading anthropological and natural history expeditions in the Andes, Amazon, and Himalaya. He brings this wealth of experience to his poetry, lectures, and workshops.</span>

