      <title>#201 - A Conversation with Yuval Noah Harari</title>
      <pubDate>Fri, 01 May 2020 20:32:46 -0400</pubDate>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">1570791</guid>
      <link>https://samharris.org/subscriber-extras/201-may-1-2020/</link>
      <itunes:subtitle/>
      <description><![CDATA[<span style="font-weight: 400;">In this episode of the podcast, Sam Harris speaks with Yuval Noah Harari about the Covid-19 pandemic and its future implications. They discuss the failures of global leadership, the widespread distrust of institutions, the benefits of nationalism and its current unraveling in the U.S., politics as a way of reconciling competing desires, the consequences of misinformation, the enduring respect for science, the future of surveillance, the changing role of religion, and other topics.</span>

<b>Yuval Noah Harari</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> has a PhD in History from the University of Oxford and lectures at the Hebrew University of Jerusalem, specializing in world history. His books have been translated into 50+ languages, with 25+ million copies sold worldwide. </span><em><a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/0062316117/ref=as_li_qf_asin_il_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=wwwsamharris03-20&amp;creative=9325&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;creativeASIN=0062316117&amp;linkId=4aea791252f5bd108d6520340669eedd" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Sapiens: A Brief History of Humankind</span></a></em><span style="font-weight: 400;"> looked deep into our past, </span><em><a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/0062464310/ref=as_li_qf_asin_il_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=wwwsamharris03-20&amp;creative=9325&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;creativeASIN=0062464310&amp;linkId=9eddc8865deb160bf4c0cb0252b31a8c" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Homo Deus: A Brief History of Tomorrow</span></a></em><span style="font-weight: 400;"> considered far-future scenarios, and </span><em><a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/0525512179/ref=as_li_qf_asin_il_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=wwwsamharris03-20&amp;creative=9325&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;creativeASIN=0525512179&amp;linkId=3a4c1d23a101aafc5989c3eabc492b93" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><span style="font-weight: 400;">21 Lessons for the 21st Century</span></a></em><span style="font-weight: 400;"> focuses on the biggest questions of the present moment.</span>

