      <description><![CDATA[<span style="font-weight: 400;">In this episode of the Making Sense podcast, Sam Harris and Paul Bloom discuss topics in the news including the tragic death of Kobe Bryant. They also explore the paradoxes of moral responsibility.</span>

<b>Paul Bloom</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> is the Brooks and Suzanne Ragen Professor of Psychology at Yale University. His research explores how children and adults understand the physical and social world, with special focus on morality, religion, fiction, and art. He has won numerous awards for his research and teaching. He is past-president of the Society for Philosophy and Psychology, and co-editor of </span><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Behavioral and Brain Sciences,</span></i><span style="font-weight: 400;"> one of the major journals in the field. Dr. Bloom has written for scientific journals such as </span><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Nature</span></i><span style="font-weight: 400;"> and </span><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Science</span></i><span style="font-weight: 400;">, and for popular outlets such as </span><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">The New York Times, The Guardian, The New Yorker,</span></i><span style="font-weight: 400;"> and </span><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">The Atlantic Monthly</span></i><span style="font-weight: 400;">. He is the author or editor of seven books, including </span><a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/0307886859/ref=as_li_qf_asin_il_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=wwwsamharris03-20&amp;creative=9325&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;creativeASIN=0307886859&amp;linkId=d7d133f93dbf1a361603bde075fca18e" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Just Babies: The Origins of Good and Evil</span></i></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> and </span><a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/0062339346/ref=as_li_qf_asin_il_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=wwwsamharris03-20&amp;creative=9325&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;creativeASIN=0062339346&amp;linkId=46f85832107f6cbb790659f03dd614d9" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Against Empathy: The Case for Rational Compassio</span></i><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">n</span></em></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span>

