      <title>#181 - The Illusory Self</title>
      <pubDate>Mon, 13 Jan 2020 19:19:32 -0500</pubDate>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">1468078</guid>
      <link>https://samharris.org/subscriber-extras/181-illusory-self/</link>
      <itunes:subtitle>A Conversation with Richard Lang</itunes:subtitle>
      <description><![CDATA[<span style="font-weight: 400;">In this episode of the Making Sense podcast, Sam Harris speaks with Richard Lang about how to experience the world beyond the illusion of the self.</span>

<b>Richard Lang</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> is a meditation teacher and writer. He was a longtime student of Douglas Harding, the author of </span><a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/1908774061/ref=as_li_qf_asin_il_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=wwwsamharris03-20&amp;creative=9325&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;creativeASIN=1908774061&amp;linkId=5a01d7fca699fce1bbc6008a5d7e295f" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">On Having No Head</span></i></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, among other books. Richard has written several books, including </span><a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/0955451264/ref=as_li_qf_asin_il_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=wwwsamharris03-20&amp;creative=9325&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;creativeASIN=0955451264&amp;linkId=37a964049462af853679c53b76902bc8" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Seeing Who You Really Are</span></i></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, </span><a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B0716TSR48/ref=as_li_qf_asin_il_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=wwwsamharris03-20&amp;creative=9325&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;creativeASIN=B0716TSR48&amp;linkId=30a1a173620d56dc2e9b1bde5b25d94c" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">The Man with No Head</span></i></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, and </span><a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/1908774509/ref=as_li_qf_asin_il_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=wwwsamharris03-20&amp;creative=9325&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;creativeASIN=1908774509&amp;linkId=a69fa8088ea4a94db3c1f0cf5790513d" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Open to the Source: Selected Teachings of Douglas Harding</span></i></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. In 1996, Richard co-founded Shollond Trust, a charity created to help share Harding’s vision as widely as possible. </span>

Website: <a href="http://www.headless.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><span style="font-weight: 400;">www.headless.org</span></a>

Twitter: <a href="https://twitter.com/headexchange" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><span style="font-weight: 400;">@headexchange</span></a>]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<span style="font-weight: 400;">In this episode of the Making Sense podcast, Sam Harris speaks with Richard Lang about how to experience the world beyond the illusion of the self.</span>

<b>Richard Lang</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> is a meditation teacher and writer. He was a longtime student of Douglas Harding, the author of </span><a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/1908774061/ref=as_li_qf_asin_il_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=wwwsamharris03-20&amp;creative=9325&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;creativeASIN=1908774061&amp;linkId=5a01d7fca699fce1bbc6008a5d7e295f" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">On Having No Head</span></i></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, among other books. Richard has written several books, including </span><a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/0955451264/ref=as_li_qf_asin_il_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=wwwsamharris03-20&amp;creative=9325&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;creativeASIN=0955451264&amp;linkId=37a964049462af853679c53b76902bc8" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Seeing Who You Really Are</span></i></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, </span><a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B0716TSR48/ref=as_li_qf_asin_il_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=wwwsamharris03-20&amp;creative=9325&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;creativeASIN=B0716TSR48&amp;linkId=30a1a173620d56dc2e9b1bde5b25d94c" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">The Man with No Head</span></i></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, and </span><a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/1908774509/ref=as_li_qf_asin_il_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=wwwsamharris03-20&amp;creative=9325&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;creativeASIN=1908774509&amp;linkId=a69fa8088ea4a94db3c1f0cf5790513d" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Open to the Source: Selected Teachings of Douglas Harding</span></i></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. In 1996, Richard co-founded Shollond Trust, a charity created to help share Harding’s vision as widely as possible. </span>

Website: <a href="http://www.headless.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><span style="font-weight: 400;">www.headless.org</span></a>

