      <description><![CDATA[In this episode of the Making Sense podcast, Sam Harris speaks with Benjamin Wittes about both volumes of the Mueller Report.

<strong>Benjamin Wittes</strong> is a legal journalist who focuses on issues of national security and law. He is a Senior Fellow in Governance Studies at the Brookings Institution, where he is the Research Director in Public Law. Benjamin is also the cofounder of Lawfare, a blog devoted to discussion of U.S. national security choices, and a cohost of the Rational Security podcast. His books include <a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/0465089747/ref=as_li_qf_asin_il_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=wwwsamharris03-20&amp;creative=9325&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;creativeASIN=0465089747&amp;linkId=7fa3bef8fb804a327f6e790eb64769f6" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><em>The Future of Violence: Robots and Germs, Hackers and Drones—Confronting A New Age of Threat</em></a> (coauthored with Gabriella Blum), <a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/0815704917/ref=as_li_qf_asin_il_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=wwwsamharris03-20&amp;creative=9325&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;creativeASIN=0815704917&amp;linkId=4aca89a2d0d3ab3a3d7816401ad54f26" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><em>Detention and Denial: The Case for Candor after Guantánamo</em></a>,  and <em><a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B001ANYE6C/ref=as_li_qf_asin_il_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=wwwsamharris03-20&amp;creative=9325&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;creativeASIN=B001ANYE6C&amp;linkId=7db485de4e3ccc1214a9011276940dff" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Law and the Long War: The Future of Justice in the Age of Terror</a></em>.

