      <link>https://samharris.org/subscriber-extras/96-nature-consciousness/</link>
      <itunes:subtitle>A Conversation with Thomas Metzinger</itunes:subtitle>
      <description><![CDATA[<strong>Thomas K. Metzinger</strong> is full professor and director of the theoretical philosophy group and the research group on neuroethics/neurophilosophy at the department of philosophy, Johannes Gutenberg University of Mainz, Germany. He is the founder and director of the MIND group and Adjunct Fellow at the Frankfurt Institute of Advanced Studies, Germany. His research centers on analytic philosophy of mind, applied ethics, philosophy of cognitive science, and philosophy of mind. He is the editor of <em>Neural Correlates of Consciousness</em> and the author of <em>Being No One</em> and <a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/0465020690?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=wwwsamharris03-20&amp;camp=1789&amp;linkCode=xm2&amp;creativeASIN=0465020690"><em>The Ego Tunnel</em></a>.]]></description>
