    <item>
      <title>#73 — Forbidden Knowledge</title>
      <pubDate>Sun, 23 Apr 2017 03:35:02 -0400</pubDate>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">1570509</guid>
      <link>https://samharris.org/subscriber-extras/73-forbidden-knowledge/</link>
      <itunes:subtitle>A Conversation with Charles Murray</itunes:subtitle>
      <description><![CDATA[<strong>Charles Murray</strong> is a political scientist and author. His 1994 <em>New York Times</em> bestseller, <a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/0684824299?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=wwwsamharris03-20&amp;camp=1789&amp;linkCode=xm2&amp;creativeASIN=0684824299"> <i>The Bell Curve</i></a> (coauthored with the late Richard J. Herrnstein), sparked heated controversy for its analysis of the role of IQ in shaping America’s class structure. Murray’s other books include <i>What It Means to Be a Libertarian, Human Accomplishment,</i> and <i>In Our Hands.</i> His 2012 book, <a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/030745343X?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=wwwsamharris03-20&amp;camp=1789&amp;linkCode=xm2&amp;creativeASIN=030745343X"><i>Coming Apart: The State of White America, 1960-2010</i></a> describes an unprecedented divergence in American classes over the last half century.

Twitter: <a href="https://twitter.com/charlesmurray">@charlesmurray</a>]]></description>
