      <title>#61 — The Power of Belief</title>
      <pubDate>Sun, 15 Jan 2017 14:04:47 -0500</pubDate>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">1570563</guid>
      <link>https://samharris.org/subscriber-extras/the-power-of-belief/</link>
      <itunes:subtitle>A Conversation with Lawrence Wright</itunes:subtitle>
      <description><![CDATA[<strong>Lawrence Wright</strong> is an author, screenwriter, playwright, and a staff writer for <i>The New Yorker</i> magazine. His works of nonfiction include <i>In the New World, Remembering Satan, The Looming Tower, Going Clear,</i> and <i>Thirteen Days in September.</i> He has also written a novel, <i>God’s Favorite.</i> His books have received many prizes and honors, including a Pulitzer Prize for <a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B003151YLU?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=wwwsamharris03-20&amp;camp=1789&amp;linkCode=xm2&amp;creativeASIN=B003151YLU"><i>The Looming Tower.</i></a> His most recent book is <a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/0385352050?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=wwwsamharris03-20&amp;camp=1789&amp;linkCode=xm2&amp;creativeASIN=0385352050"><i>The Terror Years: From al-Qaeda to the Islamic State.</i></a>]]></description>
